@Michael Woodruff Canada is doing that. (Not yet, but we're working on it. Ontario started a pilot project a year or two ago to test the idea, and it's pretty much inevitable that we'll be heading there eventually.) We also have free health care and free tuition.

So Canada is socialist, according to you. And since Canada is a better country than the US (Google the world's happiest countries, there are multiple lists showing that we far outrank you by any measurable value) that means socialism is therefore better than what you currently have. Either that or this isn't socialism.

Either way, you guys are heading in the right direction with this deal, since it contains many things that we top 10 countries already implement, which is why we're the top 10. I wish you all luck! ‚ù§
